Contributing to Wings-Core 🚀
First off, thanks for taking the time to contribute! Whether it's a bug fix, a new feature, or just fixing a typo, your help makes Wings-Core better for everyone.

How to Contribute
To keep the project organized and stable, I follow a "Review-First" workflow. This means I review every line of code before it gets merged into the main project.

1. Find or Create an Issue
Before you start coding, please check the Issues tab to see if someone is already working on the same thing. If not, feel free to open a new issue to discuss your idea!

2. Fork and Branch
Fork this repository to your own GitHub account.

Create a new branch for your work (e.g., fix-login-bug or add-color-support).

3. Make Your Changes
Keep your code clean and follow the existing style.

If you add a new CLI command, make sure to update the help text!

Note: By contributing, you agree that your code will be licensed under the AGPLv3.

4. Submit a Pull Request (PR)
Once you are ready:

Push your changes to your fork.

Open a Pull Request back to the main branch of this repository.

Describe what you changed and why.

The Review Process 🛡️
I am the primary maintainer of this project. Once you submit a PR:

I will review your code: I'll check for bugs, security issues, and overall "vibe" fit.

Feedback: I might ask you to make a few small changes or explain how something works.

Merge: Once everything looks "NICE!", I will merge your code into the official project.

Code of Conduct
Please be kind and respectful to others in the community. We're all here to build something cool together!